dc:description: Coarse pinkish clay  with cream slip.  Short nozzle missing, was rounded or heart-shaped, small stamped circle at either side of base.  Wick-hole encroaches on rim and its edge is blackened.  Plain rim separated from plain discus by moulded ring set off by grooves.  Center of discus broken.  Unpierced handle.  Two grooves on upper half.  Two circular grooves about reverse within which is incised stamp.
